<div class="entry-header">
<h2 itemprop="name">
7 free font icon tools for Bootstrap sites </h2>
<dl class="article-info">
<dt class="article-info-term"></dt>
<dd class="createdby" itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
<i class="fa fa-user"></i>
<span itemprop="name" data-toggle="tooltip" title="Written by ">Arafat Bin Sultan</span> </dd>
<dd class="category-name">
<i class="fa fa-folder-open-o"></i>
<a href="/blog" itemprop="genre" data-toggle="tooltip" title="Article Category">Blog</a> </dd>
<dd class="comment">
<i class="fa fa-comments-o"></i>
<span class="comments-anchor">
<a href="https://shapebootstrap.net/blog/57-7-free-font-icon-tools-for-bootstrap-sites#disqus_thread"></a>
</span>
</dd>
<dd class="create">
<i class="fa fa-clock-o"></i>
<time datetime="2016-03-03T15:54:39+06:00" itemprop="dateCreated" data-toggle="tooltip" title="Created Date">
03 March 2016 </time>
</dd>
<dd class="hits">
<span class="fa fa-eye"></span>
<meta itemprop="interactionCount" content="UserPageVisits:861"/>
Hits: 861</dd>
</dl>
</div>
<div itemprop="articleBody">
<p>Font icons are great alternative to PNG icons because the earlier saves web traffic and reduces page load time. Font icons are infinitely scalable, that means the graphic piece won’t break into pixels as you zoom in or view on a bigger display. With many other good things in Bootstrap, give it a boost with font icons. Here is a collection of free icon font tools.</p>
<p> </p>
<p> </p>
<h3><a href="http://fortawesome.github.io/Font-Awesome/" target="_blank">1. Font Awesome</a></h3>
<p><a href="http://fortawesome.github.io/Font-Awesome/" target="_blank"><img src="/images/2016/03/03/font-awesome.jpg" alt=""/></a></p>
<ul>
<li>Font Awesome was originally designed for Bootstrap</li>
<li>The single font contains 605 icons</li>
<li>You can style icon color, shadow, size and anything possible with CSS</li>
<li>No JavaScript required, works great on screen readers</li>
</ul>
<p> </p>
<p> </p>
<h3><a href="http://bootstrap-arrows.iarfhlaith.com/" target="_blank">2. Bootstrap Arrows</a></h3>
<p><a href="http://bootstrap-arrows.iarfhlaith.com/" target="_blank"><img src="/images/2016/03/03/bootstrap-arrows.jpg" alt=""/></a></p>
<ul>
<li>A jQuery plugin and add-on for Bootstrap </li>
<li>Basically it provides some arrows for your site, similar to its name</li>
<li>Colors of arrows can be customized</li>
<li>Arrow angle can also be adjusted</li>
</ul>
<p> </p>
<p> </p>
<h3><a href="http://fontello.com/" target="_blank">3. Fontello</a></h3>
<p><a href="http://fontello.com/" target="_blank"><img src="/images/2016/03/03/fontello.jpg" alt=""/></a></p>
<ul>
<li>The service brands itself as “icon font scissors”</li>
<li>It can help you combine webfont icons for your own projects</li>
<li>Shrink/merge symbols among multiple icon fonts</li>
<li>Offers access to a large number of professional web fonts</li>
</ul>
<p> </p>
<p> </p>
<h3><a href="http://glyphsearch.com/" target="_blank">4. GlyphSearch</a></h3>
<p><a href="http://glyphsearch.com/" target="_blank"><img src="/images/2016/03/03/glyph-search.jpg" alt=""/></a></p>
<ul>
<li>This tool lets you search icons across many icon fonts</li>
<li>Can display search results from Font Awesome, Foundation, IcoMoon, Glyphicons, Ionicons, Material Design and Octicons</li>
<li>Option for filtering search results</li>
<li>Several options for copying font icon properties</li>
</ul>
<p> </p>
<p> </p>
<h3><a href="https://design.google.com/icons/" target="_blank">5. Material Icon Font</a></h3>
<p><a href="https://design.google.com/icons/" target="_blank"><img src="/images/2016/03/03/material-icons.jpg" alt=""/></a></p>
<ul>
<li>Created by web giant Google as a part of the Material design project</li>
<li>A big growing collection of free and open source icons</li>
<li>You can download individual icons as SVG, PNG or font code</li>
<li>You can remix and re-share these icons following the license terms</li>
</ul>
<p> </p>
<p> </p>
<h3><a href="https://icomoon.io/" target="_blank">6. IcoMoon</a></h3>
<p><a href="https://icomoon.io/" target="_blank"><img src="/images/2016/03/03/icomoon.jpg" alt=""/></a></p>
<ul>
<li>More than 4000 vector icons</li>
<li>You can import your SVG files to icon fonts</li>
<li>Customization options while generating icons</li>
<li>Icon export options available to SVG, Polymer, PDF, CSH, XAML, PNG and more</li>
</ul>
<p> </p>
<p> </p>
<h3><a href="http://fontastic.me/" target="_blank">7. Fontastic</a></h3>
<p><a href="http://fontastic.me/" target="_blank"><img src="/images/2016/03/03/fontastic.jpg" alt=""/></a></p>
<ul>
<li>Fontastic is a free icon font generator</li>
<li>You can add your own icons to your collection and customize them</li>
<li>Browse and access 9000+ icons via the site</li>
<li>Quickly import font icons, update and synchronize icons on the fly</li>
</ul>
<p> </p>
<p> </p>
<p>Well, you may use these tools in other projects besides Bootstrap. Which icon font project/tool do you like most? Any suggestion for our visitors? Share via comments!</p>
<p> </p> </div>
